subSubSection.paragraph:
Discription
: Small to medium sized flies (
6.3–20.6 mm
) with brown to black body, wings entirely tomentose, and distinctive terminalia (
Figs. 5–192
), especially the roof­like epiphallus which conceals distiphallus dorsally and tubular spermatheca. 
Head:
Ventral 2/3 of face (
Fig. 1
) moderately gibbose. Palpus and proboscis yellow setose. Antenna, frons, and ocellar tubercle brown to black setose. Frons with wide stripe of long, multiple setae laterally; sides slightly converging dorsally. Ocellar tubercle with two long setae, each about as long as basal three antennomeres combined.
